      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Paul E. Utgoff</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:170px;\"><a href=\"http://people.cs.umass.edu/~utgoff/\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/5/52/Utgoff.gif\" width=\"168\" height=\"212\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Utgoff.gif\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Paul E. Utgoff <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Paul Everett Utgoff</b>, (1951 - 2008)<br />\nwas an American computer scientist and professor at Department of Computer and Information Science, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Massachusetts_Amherst\">University of Massachusetts</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amherst,_Massachusetts\">Amherst</a>. He is recognized as a pioneer in <a href=\"/Learning\" title=\"Learning\">machine learning</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_mining\">data mining</a>, and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decision_theory\">decision theory</a>, where he contributed to <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incremental_decision_tree\">incremental decision tree</a> induction, multivariate decision trees <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, and problem representation. He received his Ph.D. in 1984 from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rutgers%E2%80%93New_Brunswick\">Rutgers–New Brunswick</a> on <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inductive_bias\">inductive bias</a> in machine learning under supervision of <a href=\"/Tom_Mitchell\" title=\"Tom Mitchell\">Tom Mitchell</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saul_Amarel\">Saul Amarel</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>.  In 1993, he designed the <i>Incremental Tree Inducer</i> (<b>ITI</b>) program and a new algorithm called <i>Direct-Metric Tree Inducer</i> (<b>DMTI</b>) made feasible by the ability to restructure trees efficiently <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p><p>Paul E. Utgoff died on October 11, 2008 at the age of 57 due to complications from surgery that he elected to undergo as part of his battle against <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Appendix_cancer\">appendiceal cancer</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#1980_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1980 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#1990_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1990 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paul_E._Utgoff&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1980_...\">1980 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paul_E._Utgoff&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: 1980 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a>, <a href=\"/Tom_Mitchell\" title=\"Tom Mitchell\">Tom Mitchell</a> (<b>1982</b>). <i>Acquisition of Appropriate Bias for Inductive Concept Learning</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/aaai/aaai82.html#UtgoffM82\">AAAI 1982</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.aaai.org/Papers/AAAI/1982/AAAI82-099.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a> (<b>1984</b>). <i>Shift of Bias for Inductive Concept Learning</i>. Ph.D. thesis, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rutgers%E2%80%93New_Brunswick\">Rutgers University, New Brunswick</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a> (<b>1988</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=896712\">ID5: An incremental ID3</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/icml/ml1988.html#Utgoff88\">ML 1988</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a> (<b>1989</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1023%2FA%3A1022699900025\">Incremental Induction of Decision Trees</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_Learning_%28journal%29\">Machine Learning</a>, Vol. 4</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1990_...\">1990 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paul_E._Utgoff&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 1990 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#CEBrodley\" title=\"Mathematician\">Carla E. Brodley</a> (<b>1990</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=101891\">An Incremental Method for Finding Multivariate Splits for Decision Trees</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/icml/ml1990.html#UtgoffB90\">ML 1990</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/y/Yee:Richard_C=\">Richard C. Yee</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/s/Saxena:Sharad\">Sharad Saxena</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a>, <a href=\"/Andrew_Barto\" title=\"Andrew Barto\">Andrew Barto</a> (<b>1990</b>). <i>Explaining Temporal Differences to Create Useful Concepts for Evaluating States</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/aaai/aaai90.html#YeeSUB90\">AAAI 1990</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.aaai.org/Papers/AAAI/1990/AAAI90-132.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dblp.uni-trier.de/pers/hd/c/Clouse:Jeffery_A=\">Jeffery A. Clouse</a> (<b>1991</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://scholarworks.umass.edu/cs_faculty_pubs/193/\">Two Kinds of Training Information for Evaluation Function Learning</a></i>.  <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Massachusetts_Amherst\">University of Massachusetts, Amherst</a>, Proceedings of the AAAI 1991</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a> (<b>1994</b>). <i>An Improved Algorithm for Incremental Induction of Decision Trees</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/icml/icml1994.html#Utgoff94\">ICML 1994</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/summary?doi=10.1.1.54.5089\">CiteSeerX</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Mathematician#CEBrodley\" title=\"Mathematician\">Carla E. Brodley</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a> (<b>1995</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://link.springer.com/article/10.1023%2FA%3A1022607123649\">Multivariate Decision Trees</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_Learning_%28journal%29\">Machine Learning</a>, Vol. 19, No. 1</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a>, <a href=\"/Doina_Precup\" title=\"Doina Precup\">Doina Precup</a> (<b>1998</b>). <i>Constructive Function Approximation</i>. Chapter in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.springer.com/gb/book/9780792381969\">Feature Extraction, Construction, and Selection: A Data-Mining Perspective</a>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wolters_Kluwer\">Kluwer</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=David_J._Stracuzzi&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"David J. Stracuzzi (page does not exist)\">David J. Stracuzzi</a> (<b>1999</b>). <i>Approximation Via Value Unification</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/icml/icml1999.html#UtgoffS99\">ICML 1999</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.5.1394&amp;rep=rep1&amp;type=pdf\">pdf</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paul_E._Utgoff&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a>, <a href=\"/Richard_P._Cochran\" title=\"Richard P. Cochran\">Richard P. Cochran</a> (<b>2000</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/3-540-45579-5_1\">A Least-Certainty Heuristic for Selective Search</a></i>. <a href=\"/CG_2000\" title=\"CG 2000\">CG 2000</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.cs.umass.edu/~utgoff/papers/springer-lcf.pdf\">pdf</a>&#160;» <a href=\"/Richard_P._Cochran#LCF\" title=\"Richard P. Cochran\">LCF</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/index.php?title=David_J._Stracuzzi&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"David J. Stracuzzi (page does not exist)\">David J. Stracuzzi</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a> (<b>2000</b>). <i>Feature compilation</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Massachusetts_Amherst\">University of Massachusetts Amherst</a>, TR-00-18, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.stracuzzi.info/david/manuscripts/tr-00-18.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=David_J._Stracuzzi&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"David J. Stracuzzi (page does not exist)\">David J. Stracuzzi</a> (<b>2002</b>). <i>Many-Layered Learning</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neural_Computation_%28journal%29\">Neural Computation</a>, Vol. 14, No. 10, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.cs.umass.edu/~utgoff/papers/neco-stl.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Doina_Precup\" title=\"Doina Precup\">Doina Precup</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Classification using Phi-Machines and Constructive Function Approximation</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_Learning_%28journal%29\">Machine Learning</a>, Vol. 55</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=David_J._Stracuzzi&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"David J. Stracuzzi (page does not exist)\">David J. Stracuzzi</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Randomized Variable Elimination</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Journal_of_Machine_Learning_Research\">Journal of Machine Learning Research</a>, Vol. 5, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.jmlr.org/papers/volume5/stracuzzi04a/stracuzzi04a.pdf\">pdf</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paul_E._Utgoff&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.cs.umass.edu/~utgoff/\">Paul Utgoff</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://genealogy.math.ndsu.nodak.edu/id.php?id=70261\">The Mathematics Genealogy Project - Paul Utgoff</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.cs.umass.edu/~lrn/iti/index.html\">Machine Learning Laboratory - Incremental Decision Tree Induction</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.game-ai-forum.org/icga-tournaments/person.php?id=164\">Paul Utgoff's ICGA Tournaments</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paul_E._Utgoff&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://people.cs.umass.edu/~utgoff/\">Paul Utgoff</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://scholar.google.com/citations?user=sQ8u6h4AAAAJ\">Carla E. Brodley</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a> (<b>1995</b>). <i>Multivariate Decision Trees</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Machine_Learning_%28journal%29\">Machine Learning</a>, Vol. 19, No. 1</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Paul E. Utgoff</a> (<b>1984</b>). <i>Shift of Bias for Inductive Concept Learning</i>. Ph.D. thesis, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rutgers%E2%80%93New_Brunswick\">Rutgers University, New Brunswick</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span 